International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri 19 Jul 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ontario Ministry of Health and Long Term Care, West Nile Virus
Bulletin, Fri 19 Jul 2002 [edited]
<http://www.gov.on.ca/health/english/program/pubhealth/wnv_mn.html>

Ontario: West Nile Virus-positive Bird Total Rises to 17
---------------------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health and Long-Term Care works with local public health
units and Health Canada to monitor the presence of West Nile virus (WNV) in
the province.
As of Fri 19 Jul 2002, 16 birds have been confirmed positive and one
presumed positive for WNV in Ontario, as follows:
Peel Region, 3 confirmed (collected 19 May to 9 Jul 2002); Oxford Region, 2
confirmed (collected 4 Jun to 8 Jul 2002); Chatham-Kent Region, 5 confirmed
(collected 12 to 14 Jun 2002); Middlesex-London Region, 1 confirmed
(collected 17 Jun 2002); Halton Region, 2 confirmed (collected 15 Jun to 7
Jul 2002); Windsor-Essex, 1 confirmed (collected 18 Jun 2002); Perth, 2
(collected 2 Jul to 8 Jul 2002); Toronto, 1 presumed positive (3 Jul 2002).
The presence of West Nile virus in Canada was confirmed first on 22 Aug
2001 in a bird submitted from Windsor-Essex Country. Neither the virus nor
its symptoms have been detected in humans to date.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Since Tue 12 Jul 2002, 5 more West Nile virus-positive birds (Peel 2,
Oxford 1, Halton 1, Perth 1) and one presumed positive bird (Toronto) have
been recorded in Ontario. - Mod.CP]
